result.execSummary:
The defendant Aportier Maurice Weeks Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Repeater, Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Repeater, Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

AS TO COUNT 1:   COURT ORDERED the Defendant to serve 1 YEAR, STRAIGHT TIME, in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, and as to Count 2, with credit for 108 days time served.  
COURT ORDERED the DNA charge to be paid witn in two years of today's date.  Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.  Court ordered Defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

AS TO COUNT 3:    COURT SENTENCED the Defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 3 YEARS, with credit for 0 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 18 MONTHS, to run consecutive to any other Sentence, if revoked on any violation Count 2 will run consecutive to Count 1.  

The Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration or the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Programs.

The Court IMPOSED AND STAYED this sentence and placed the Defendant on probation for a period of 24 MONTHS with the following conditions:  
*  No new law violations reaching the level of a probable cause finding.
*  Cooperate with agent.
*  Pay costs, surcharges, assessments, domestic, supervision fees out of bail, if any, or during the period of probation.  If revoked, Defendant shall pay up to 25% of prison funds with the balance due prior to the end of the Extended supervision. Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.

*  No contact with the victim unless approved by the Court and or agent.
*  3rd party contact for the purposes of time with children as approved by the agent.
